text:
BREAKING: Look at this.

A new crypto account was opened yesterday morning.

30 minutes BEFORE Trump's announcement of 100% tariffs on China, it added a huge multi-million dollar levered Bitcoin short position, per YF.

The market dumped.

The trader made a profit of $192 million in two hours.

Unusual.

show_title: Sonic Clanker Logos & Market Meltdowns: GM Farcaster ep298
text:
if you survived and preserved your money, you're already doing great. If you made money from this flash-crash, congratulations - you‚Äôre better than 90% of the market. 

Interestingly, just a few hours before this drop, the Trump team's token $WLFI was sold off by 30% to have funds to buy it back from panicking people. 

Also, if you were following the news, you had time to accept the current losses and close all long positions before the global drop; it didn‚Äôt happen all at once. Watch the market for a few more days; don‚Äôt jump in due to FOMO and rush to trade. It‚Äôs better to miss out on some profits than to incur losses.

P.S. Here‚Äôs how those insider sales of $WLFI looked on the chart before the drop.

show_title: Sonic Clanker Logos & Market Meltdowns: GM Farcaster ep298
text:
Hopefully, the past 24 hours in crypto will motivate a flight to quality.

This industry doesn‚Äôt need the long tail of griftcoins; just a handful of blue chips with utility. It doesn‚Äôt need shady CEXes and DEXes that fold under stress; only credible players that have shown Lindyness. And it certainly doesn‚Äôt need zero-sum PvP games, but instead positive-sum attitudes toward building responsibly.

I see a silver lining to this flash crash, in the form of garbage collection. I low-key wish the altcoin market doesn‚Äôt recover and that we can move on without it.

May we come out of this with more computer and less casino

text:
I‚Äôve updated my Farcaster Bull case. 

Everyone seems to have their opinion about what FC is for or what it should be about. 

‚ÄúIt‚Äôs for Base maxis.‚Äù

‚ÄúIt‚Äôs just for devs/builders.‚Äù

‚ÄúIt‚Äôs all crypto bros.‚Äù

But time and again, the casts that go viral and resonate with the most people are authentic, human stories that bare truths about the writer. 

The uniqueness of this phenomenon can‚Äôt be understated, especially as the internet continues to ossify over the generative corpse of its once-lived existence. 

The dead internet theory doesn‚Äôt apply on Farcaster. 

IMO, that‚Äôs its greatest strength. You can still find and connect with real people from a diverse spectrum of backgrounds. 

What you do with those connections can form life-altering bonds. 

That‚Äôs not possible anywhere else online.
